### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

core

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

When an click is happen in child component then all the parents gets re-rendered (getting refreshView). Which could lead to performance issue. 
So if child component have 
1. <button (click)="..." >Test</button> OR
2. @Hostbinding  
then whole tree till top gets refreshed.


Please check attached component file. 
As seen that all components have ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush. When button is clicked in ChildLevel2Component then AppComponents gets refreshed (re-rendered). Example shows that ngAfterViewChecked and logger methods get called on AppComponent.

Commented code of @Hostbinding causing the same issue. 

